    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-04-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-04-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="239"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d239">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">150.071 Control/24</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">German Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>On January 21st 1928 the Embassy had the honor to inform the Department of
                        State<note n="69" xml:id="d239fn69">
                        <ref target="frus1928v01#pg_843">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1928, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 843</ref>.</note> of the apprehension
                    felt by the German Government with regard to ‘the former Senate Bill 717 “to
                    provide for the deportation of certain Alien seamen, and for other
                    purposes”.</p>
                <p>The considerations submitted in this respect also pertain to the’ bills S. 202,
                    S. 1941 and H.R. 7763 introduced in the present 71st Congress, as any such
                    legislation would, in the opinion of the German Government, entail serious
                    difficulties to the German American shipping trade.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-04-15">April 15,
                            1930</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
